{ {Local Crafts. }
A few people in Quarff work at crafts or small industry. Karen-Anne's mother grafts jumpers. She grafts necks and cuffs. Sometimes she puts pockets on the jumpers. She gives them to a man who sells them. Most women in Quarff are expert knitters. An old man in Quarff does leatherwork. He makes purses, bags and mends shoes. Malcolm's mother cures sheepskins for sale. There is also a man who makes furniture; he will design and produce whatever you want. Lynn, Lyall and Russell's dad is a builder; he builds garages and houses.
KAREN-ANNE ANDERSON.
